I.     Requirements
  
  -Mouse
  -MS DOS ?.??-6.22

II.    Command Line Paramaters
  
  To Have ARKEDIT Open The NES File you need to have the NES File name
  for an argument.

  example:

  ARKEDIT ARKANOID
  ARKEDIT ARKANOID.NES

  The .NES Pramater is optional.

III.   Basic Editing

  Editing is quite simple.  After your ROM has loaded Click on an desginated
  Block or Block position on the editor to the left.  After you click there
  either 2 options will apear at the Bottom:

  ADD or DEL

  Clicking ADD will add a block at the current position.
  Clicking DEL will Delete the block at the current position.

  If there was a block there you can do any of the other following:

  Change Hits
  Change Capsul Status
  Change Pallete
  Change Style (1 normal block & 2 3D blocks like the unbreakable ones
                in Arkanoid)
  Change Which Palette To Use (A is top Palette B is Bottom)

  ***Please Note Palette "F" can only be used for Unbreakable Blocks!!!
  ***Also not the Higher the Palette the more points the Block is worth!!!

  At Any Time You Can Click On The Palettes to Change Them.
  *****MUST NOTE ABOUT PALETTES!!!*****
  This Current Editor Doesn't let you lay out the back Palette yet.
  hopefully the next version will.

  Please also not when Changing Levels it DOES NOT auto ave the last level.
  You Must Click On Save To Be able to Save it!!!

